meals.ingredients:
- 2 cups of dried York or Pedrosillano garbanzo beans: rinse, soak overnight, and drain;
- 1 cup of cilantro, chopped;
- ½ small white onion, diced;
- 2 garlic cloves;
- 1 small chili pepper, finely diced;
- 1 tablespoon of coriander;
- 1 tablespoon of cumin;
- 1 teaspoon of baking soda;
- 1/2 teaspoon of kosher salt;
- canola oil for frying.

- 300 ml of almond milk;
- 1 teaspoon of vanilla extract;
- 75 g of blanched almonds;
- 100 g of buckwheat flour;
- 100 g of rice flour;
- 2 level teaspoons of baking powder;
- 1 ripe banana;
- olive oil;
- 350 g of seasonal berries, such as strawberries, blackberries, raspberries, blueberries;
- 1 sprig of fresh rosemary;
- maple syrup;
- 4 tablespoons of Greek yogurt, optional.

- 2 tablespoons of baby capers in brine;
- 2 lemons;
- extra virgin olive oil;
- 1 clove of garlic;
- 1 fresh red chili;
- 4 anchovy fillets in oil, from sustainable sources;
- 30 g of shelled unsalted pistachios;
- ½ of a bunch of fresh mint, (15g);
- 4 large squid, cleaned, gutted, from sustainable sources;
- 500 g of large ripe tomatoes.

- 100 g of fine rice noodles;
- 2 x 120 g of skinless free-range chicken breasts; - groundnut oil;
- 4 spring onions;
- ½ a Chinese cabbage (150g);
- 200 g of sugar snap peas;
- ½–1 fresh red chili;
- 2 limes;
- 1 tablespoon of low-salt soy sauce;
- 1 tablespoon of peanut butter;
- 2 tablespoons of natural yogurt;
- 2 cm piece of ginger;
- 2 teaspoons of sesame seeds.

- 160 g of ripe cherry tomatoes, on the vine;
- 4 thin slices of wholemeal bread (35 g each);
- 3 large free-range eggs;
- 1 x 15 g slice of higher-welfare smoked ham;
- 80 g of baby spinach;
- 2 tablespoons of semi-skimmed milk;
- 1 heaped tablespoon of cottage cheese;
- extra virgin olive oil;
- hot chili sauce.

- 200 g of blanched hazelnuts;
- 200 g of Medjool dates;
- 400 g of porridge oats;
- 2 teaspoons of vanilla extract;
- 3 heaped tablespoons of quality cocoa powder;
- 1 orange.
For each portion:
- 200 ml of coconut water;
- 1 heaped tablespoon of Greek yogurt;
- 80 g of fresh fruit, such as raspberries, blackberries, sliced banana, grated apple, pear, and segments of orange;
- 1 pinch of ground cinnamon or quality cocoa powder (optional).

- 100 g of dried fruit, such as sultanas, raisins, dried apricots;
- 50 g of mixed unsalted nuts, such as almonds, hazelnuts, walnuts;
- 50 g of mixed seeds, such as pumpkin, sunflower, sesame, poppy;
- 400 g of porridge oats;
